reviews.text: Beautiful station in Hythe. Feels like you’ve stepped back in time! Gardens are really well tended to and looked after. If you’re taller though mind your head when standing near the edge of the platform as there big bits of metal hanging off. Nearly scalped myself!
Only one review for this station that is known worldwide! Brilliant. Bring the kids. Bring the grandparents. Bring an anorak. Could do with being cheaper.

The conductor saw my girlfriend running out of the toilet to catch the train and blew the whistle, even after I asked him to wait 30 seconds for her.
It's not Japan railways, it's supposed to be a tourists attraction.
I've been a few times before when I was young but that kind of jobsworth attitude has made sure I'll never go again.
Great railway line good food but pricey in the gift shop
A nice day out and would recommend the Light House at Dungeness if you go all the way. Prices are a bit steep though, particularly in the gift shop.
